{"version":"https://jsonfeed.org/version/1","title":"Hacker News: Newest","description":"Hacker News RSS","home_page_url":"https://news.ycombinator.com/newest","items":[{"id":"https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=47368135","title":"Digg is gone again","content_html":"\n\u003cp\u003eArticle URL: \u003ca href=\"https://digg.com/\"\u003ehttps://digg.com/\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eComments URL: \u003ca href=\"https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=47368135\"\u003ehttps://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=47368135\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003ePoints: 104\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e# Comments: 78\u003c/p\u003e\n","url":"https://digg.com/","external_url":"https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=47368135","date_published":"2026-03-13T18:52:17Z","author":{"name":"hammerbrostime","url":"https://news.ycombinator.com/user?id=hammerbrostime"}},{"id":"https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=47368033","title":"Mouser: An open source alternative to Logi-Plus mouse software","content_html":"\n\u003cp\u003eI discovered this project because all-of-a-sudden Logi Options Plus software updater started taking 40-60% of my Intel Macbook Pro until I killed the process (of course it restarts). In my searches I ended up at a reddit discussion where I found other people with same issues.\u003cp\u003eI'm a minor contributor to this project but it aims to reduce/eliminate the need to use Logitech proprietary software and telemetry. We could use help if other people are interested.\u003cp\u003ePlease check out the github link for more detailed motivations (eliminating telemetry) as a part of this project.   Here is link: \u003ca href=\"https://github.com/TomBadash/MouseControl\" rel=\"nofollow\"\u003ehttps://github.com/TomBadash/MouseControl\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003chr\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eComments URL: \u003ca href=\"https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=47368033\"\u003ehttps://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=47368033\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003ePoints: 147\u0